rmation.”\n\n---\n\n### Key distinction\n\nAn **elastic automator** usually manages **resources**.\n\nAn **RPA bot** usually performs **tasks**.\n\nSo:\n\n> Elastic automator = “Scale the system when demand changes.”  \n> RPA bot = “Do repetitive work that a person would normally do.”  \n\nThey can work together, though. For example, if many invoices need processing, an elastic automator could start more RPA bots to handle the increased workload.",
